{
  "texts": [
    "In Fig. 3H, I, we show regimes for successful retrieval of MF examples, PP examples, and PP concepts.",
    "For MF and PP examples, the network has a capacity for stored patterns above which they can no longer be retrieved (Fig. 3H).",
    "For PP concepts, the network requires storage of a minimum number of examples below which concepts cannot be built.",
    "As expected intuitively, fewer examples are needed if they are more correlated, since common features can be more easily deduced.",
    "Figure 3I overlays retrieval regimes for MF examples and PP concepts."
  ]
}